<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-21T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-21T20:00:00-05:00" n="177" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.154/12–1644: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-21T21:00:00-04:00">December
                                    21, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>441. Authorization requested in your telegrams 533 and 534 of December 16
                            is granted. Public Roads states that none of the $65,000 should be used
                            by Dominicans to purchase additional equipment, since sufficient
                            equipment for completion of road has long been available to them, and
                            that expense of any such equipment should be met by Dominican
                            Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>